thank you letter following the interview background i was an intern for this small person staff nonprofit organization last year after submitting two mock projects i was asked to come in for an interview with my mentor it was a great interview and now i'm contemplating the thank you letter following the interview as a stay at home mom for now after my son goes to bed i usually have around hours to use for me and i enjoy making thank you cards i'm bored what can i say anyway i was wondering if it would proper for me to make a professional looking thank you card in other words no blues clues allowed and print the letter on the inside of the card thoughts i didn't make it clear i'm interviewing for a full time position not another internship just in case you were confused thanks to you all i don't want to sound too simplistic or idiotic and i appreciate all of your comments it's a nice thought but it will most likely be viewed as unprofessional the vast majority of thank you notes are now sent via email i've been in hr for over years and mailed thank yous are rare managers prefer email they can keep an easier dialogue The Apprentice 2 E-mail Paul Is Dead Plame affair Karl Rove Make money fast On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences Calvin and Hobbes Appeal Cindy Sheehan I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Infantilism Time Out of Mind Crossword The Shining (film) Advance fee fraud Homestar Runner Poker jargon Hiberno-English 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy, voting machines Social rule Negima The Jazz Singer Apostrophe (mark) Trombone Martin Heidegger Walt Disney World College Program George F. Kennan Steven Wright Quotation mark Esperanto as an international language Ocean's Twelve Trigun Online Copyright Infringement Liability Limitation Act Mail Architect Shaggy dog story Richard Feynman Spam (electronic) Esperanto orthography Scientology beliefs and practices Gaia Online Baseball Blood on the Tracks United States Postal Service Ron and Fez Killian documents Eter